<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="79d8b640-08e8-5fd3-897e-bb692de8464a" activityNameId="95461946-7b68-4a67-b954-d0070a0677ef" parentActivityId="265006e4-eef1-5d25-9cac-fedb3da09504" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cationic resin production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">cation exchange resin</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">strong acidic cation exchange resin</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">SAC</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">cation resin</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of cation-exchange resin. The raw materials and chemicals used for production are included, as well as estimated emissions and wastes from production (incomplete), and estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of moist cation-exchange resin which is used for water treatment. The moisture content of the assessed resins is 50 wt%, corresponding to a resin with 6-8 wt% divinylbenzene (DVB) crosslinking. The bulk density of the moist (hydrated) resin is 1.28 kg/L.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Due to a lack of production data, this dataset is based on stoichiometric calculations, as well approximations based on data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="4a11cbd4-74bf-47fb-9fe5-6e97e3db136b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2013:Manufacture of plastics and synthetic rubber in primary forms</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="131278d6-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">CH</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset models the production of a strong acidic cation exchanger resin (hydrogen form) for water treatment, with a process yield of 95%.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The production process starts with the polymerisation of the styrene and divinylbenzene (DVB), which are used as a cross-linking agent and are mixed in a suspension system. This process leads to hardened spherical plastic beads. Standard resins used for water treatment processes are 8 wt-% DVB cross-linked. In this inventory the production of this cross-linked copolymer beads was approximated with linear polystyrene.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">The copolymer is then dried and screened to meet the resin specifications. The next production step is the sulfonation of the copolymer to produce the functional groups needed for ion exchange. In this step the copolymer is treated with concentrated sulphuric acid or chlorosulfonic acid under elevated temperatures (about 80 °C). The last step consists in rinsing the functionalized copolymer. This is performed by hot water washing and steaming the resin to reduce the amount of organic compounds left in the resin from the manufacturing process. At this point, the cation resin is in the hydrogen form which is the form desired for this inventory. If the resin is needed in a sodium form (Na+), it has to be neutralised with NaOH. This neutralisation step is not included in this inventory.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Reference:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="1997-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time of literature publication. Measurements took place partly before this period. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="3c8567cf-7783-5c30-bfee-ae2f0887b46c" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="RP" amount="1.0" intermediateExchangeId="1fe6463a-08c8-406e-b05c-d5ad845da6be" productionVolumeAmount="0.04" productionVolumeVariableName="RP_PV">
        <name xml:lang="en">cationic resin</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Acidic cation exchanger resin (hydrogen form) is mostly used for water treatment activities.

References:
Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</comment>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.26080293256189" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon allocation</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a301a838-7975-4d89-9e74-8eb77ad03cd1" amount="0.52160586512378" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="c74c3729-e577-4081-b572-a283d2561a75" amount="0.52160586512378" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Chemically inert polystyrene beads are treated with concentrated sulfuric or chlorosulfonic acid to give cross-linked polystyrene 3-sulfonic acid (Cation exchange resins, Ullmann). The resine was approximated as C8H8O3S (from Ullmann, Cation exchange resins). The resine is hydrated (ecoinvent v2.2 report 8, part II, Tab 93.5)</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6393c14b-db78-445d-a47b-c0cb866a1b25" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="3a0af1d6-04c3-41c6-a3da-92c4f61e0eaa" amount="0.5" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">dry mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">resine is hydrated (ecoinvent v2.2 report 8, part II, Tab 93.5)</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="48c987bb-3144-4872-b5c7-b1389c40be25" amount="6.68" mathematicalRelation="" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e">
          <name xml:lang="en">heating value, net</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">LHV is calculated based on the Carbon content of the product. More details can be found on the respective documentation.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="1.6" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Estimated to have the same price as anionic resin which was calculated from EU prices by use of exchange rates.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a9358458-9724-4f03-b622-106eda248916" amount="1.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
