        </property>
        <property propertyId="67f102e2-9cb6-4d20-aa16-bf74d8a03326" amount="1.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">wet mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">This is a placeholder value that does not reflect real-world production volumes. This dataset does not currently require a real-world production volume to work in the database framework, and no actual data were collected yet. This has no negative effect on the results of the ecoinvent database. The placeholder value of this activity was estimated by scaling the global production volume (which is also a placeholder value) according to the sales of chemicals products reported by Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council), and the American Chemistry Council.
According to Cefic (2016) the global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per region are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, which amount to 518.7 billion euros out of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported by the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to which the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016.

References:
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html</productionVolumeComment>
